div.p: which I do not forward at once, as I expect there will be some more telegraphing.

I go away this day to Tasmania, but Mr Rasmus Parelius, who will act as Consul for Sweden and Norway during my absence, will immediately forward to Sweden any message that the Committee transmits to the Consulate, and in every respect do what I could have done myself.
